The paper deals with parallel graph algorithms, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on space complexity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-category. The use of the Massive Parallel Computation (MPC) model and the mention of classic PRAM algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the mention of finding a maximal independent set in bounded-arboricity graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
